    "narrative": "For April 30, our primary offensive engine is anchored by **Daulton Varsho** (65.73) and **Tyler Freeman** (61.81). **Daulton Varsho** benefits significantly from a favorable matchup against Bailey Ober, combined with a strong platoon edge and an optimized spot in the lineup. Similarly, **Tyler Freeman** thrives today due to a combination of moderate park factors and a high-probability SB environment; specifically, the opposing pitcher\u2019s slow delivery gives him an actionable boost in our scarce stolen base category. **Yainer Diaz** (60.78) also provides a solid foundation, leveraging a significant park factor boost that helps mitigate the risk presented by a mid-tier arm like Bassitt.\n\nThe bench decision process was most contested regarding **Masyn Winn** (42.21), who fell just shy of our starting threshold. While **Masyn Winn** benefits from favorable wind conditions, the matchup against Skenes\u2014an elite arm\u2014ultimately rendered his efficiency metrics too volatile compared to the safer profiles of **Gleyber Torres** or **Bryson Stott**. Speaking of **Bryson Stott**, he remains a high-value utility play; despite the tough matchup against Logan Webb, the aggressive stolen base potential against a slow-working battery, paired with a positive platoon split, keeps him well above our floor. \n\nCaution is advised regarding the \"Lineup Pending\" status for **Geraldo Perdomo**, **Daulton Varsho**, **Lawrence Butler**, and **Drew Gilbert**. Their scores are predicated on these assumed batting positions, and any drop in the order could erode their value. We are also wary of the heavy reliance on **Luis Arraez** and **Matt Chapman** against S\u00e1nchez; while their base projections are sound, the negative impact of the platoon and the tough opposing SP skill leaves little margin for error today. We continue to monitor for any late-breaking weather or lineup changes that could shift the strategy for **Jeremiah Jackson** and **Taylor Ward**, both of whom are projected for high-scoring environments but face specific platoon hurdles.",
